# eDNA Database Comparison Code

This repository contains the R scripts used for the eDNA database comparison manuscript. The scripts have been cleaned for public release: comments are in English, repeated code has been moved into reusable functions, and local absolute paths have been replaced by configurable data and output directories.

## Repository Layout

| Script | Purpose |
| --- | --- |
| `scripts/01_bray_curtis_similarity.R` | Calculates site-level Bray-Curtis similarity between morphology and eDNA family-level matrices. |
| `scripts/02_family_venn_diagram.R` | Draws an area-proportional family-level Euler/Venn diagram for CMBL, NCBI, and morphology datasets. |
| `scripts/03_loocv_random_forest_wqi.R` | Runs random forest LOOCV for WQI prediction with training-set CSS normalization and fold-wise feature selection. |
| `scripts/04_wqi_regression.R` | Plots measured vs. predicted WQI, exports model metrics, and optionally runs weighted Kappa and environmental correlation plots. |
| `scripts/05_site_rarefaction_curves.R` | Draws site-level rarefaction curves for raw, CMBL-annotated, and NCBI-annotated OTU matrices. |
| `scripts/06_otu_importance_barplot.R` | Draws horizontal bar plots for important OTUs, colored by class. |
| `scripts/_shared.R` | Shared helpers for package checks, paths, data loading, and simple metrics. |

## Data

Raw data and manuscript files are not included in this code repository. By default, scripts look for input files in a local `data/` folder and write outputs to `outputs/<analysis-name>/`.

You can also set environment variables before running the scripts:

```r
Sys.setenv(EDNA_DATA_DIR = "path/to/input/data")
Sys.setenv(EDNA_OUTPUT_DIR = "path/to/output/folder")
```

Several scripts also support file-specific environment variables, such as `MORPHOLOGY_FAMILY_FILE`, `EDNA_FAMILY_FILE`, `CMBL_FAMILY_FILE`, `WQI_OTU_FILE`, `WQI_PREDICTION_FILE`, and `OTU_IMPORTANCE_FILE`.

## Packages

Install the required R packages before running the scripts:

```r
install.packages(c(
  "dplyr",
  "ggplot2",
  "ggpubr",
  "gridExtra",
  "irr",
  "RColorBrewer",
  "ranger",
  "vegan",
  "eulerr"
))

if (!requireNamespace("BiocManager", quietly = TRUE)) {
  install.packages("BiocManager")
}

BiocManager::install(c("metagenomeSeq", "Biobase"))
```

The environmental-correlation section of `04_wqi_regression_and_kappa.R` additionally uses `mice` when environmental input files are available.

## Example

From the repository root:

```r
source("scripts/01_bray_curtis_similarity.R")
```

or from a terminal:

```sh
Rscript scripts/01_bray_curtis_similarity.R
```

